			<td class="trow2 post_content ">
				<span class="smalltext"><strong>RE: How to deal with disappointed family? </strong></span>

				<div class="post_body" id="pid_212490">
					Kudos, Noelani, for coming out...<br />
<br />
As long as you're not willfully causing harm/distress (and I think you're not), try to remember that they are responsible for their feelings and reactions to your news.<br />
<br />
Likewise, you're responsible for yours....you can choose to feel guilty...which doesn't feel like much of a choice for us kindhearted folks...or you can bask in your freedom.  <br />
<br />
Try simply telling them that you're sad for their sadness, but that you're happy, and tell them the things that bring joy and meaning to your life.  Tell them since you're happy, they have the freedom to be happy.<br />
<br />
Good luck!
				</div>
				
				<div class="post_sig">
